WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.104 align:middle line:90%


00:00:11.104 --> 00:00:11.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA GARR: Hi.

00:00:11.770 --> 00:00:13.603 align:middle line:10%
I'm Lisa Garr, host of
"Gaiam Inspirations,"

00:00:13.603 --> 00:00:15.480 align:middle line:10%
and we are broadcasting
live from downtown

00:00:15.480 --> 00:00:17.900 align:middle line:10%
Denver, Colorado at the
Hay House "I Can Do It!"

00:00:17.900 --> 00:00:18.689 align:middle line:10%
conference.

00:00:18.689 --> 00:00:19.980 align:middle line:90%
And let me ask you a questions.

00:00:19.980 --> 00:00:22.850 align:middle line:84%
Is this-- you, do you identify
with this-- that you really,

00:00:22.850 --> 00:00:25.730 align:middle line:84%
really want to learn
how to meditate,

00:00:25.730 --> 00:00:27.790 align:middle line:90%
maybe tried to meditate before?

00:00:27.790 --> 00:00:30.970 align:middle line:84%
You want to be less reactive
in stressful situations?

00:00:30.970 --> 00:00:36.010 align:middle line:84%
But you can't just seem to
sit still and empty your mind?

00:00:36.010 --> 00:00:38.030 align:middle line:84%
I know exactly what
you're talking about.

00:00:38.030 --> 00:00:39.970 align:middle line:84%
Well, it could be
because you just

00:00:39.970 --> 00:00:43.000 align:middle line:84%
haven't found the right
meditation style for you.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:45.200 align:middle line:84%
And according to
my guest, davidji,

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:46.780 align:middle line:84%
who is a meditation
teacher and has

00:00:46.780 --> 00:00:48.770 align:middle line:84%
been an apprentice
to Deepak Chopra

00:00:48.770 --> 00:00:51.440 align:middle line:84%
for nearly a decade
at the Chopra Center,

00:00:51.440 --> 00:00:54.020 align:middle line:84%
he says that not
one size fits all

00:00:54.020 --> 00:00:56.609 align:middle line:84%
where it comes to meditation,
and all you need to do

00:00:56.609 --> 00:00:58.400 align:middle line:84%
is find the right style
that works for you.

00:00:58.400 --> 00:01:01.240 align:middle line:84%
So thank you for being
here and enlightening us.

00:01:01.240 --> 00:01:02.600 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Thank you, Lisa.

00:01:02.600 --> 00:01:04.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And this
whole conversation.

00:01:04.100 --> 00:01:06.442 align:middle line:84%
So let me just ask you, first
of all, you didn't always

00:01:06.442 --> 00:01:08.150 align:middle line:84%
start off as a meditation
teacher, right?

00:01:08.150 --> 00:01:09.733 align:middle line:84%
You were in corporate
America, and you

00:01:09.733 --> 00:01:11.160 align:middle line:90%
did the whole corporate world.

00:01:11.160 --> 00:01:12.510 align:middle line:90%
Tell me a little bit about that.

00:01:12.510 --> 00:01:14.830 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: I started
meditating back in college.

00:01:14.830 --> 00:01:16.260 align:middle line:90%
And it was a Zen meditation.

00:01:16.260 --> 00:01:17.510 align:middle line:10%
There were 12 of us.

00:01:17.510 --> 00:01:20.940 align:middle line:10%
We were instructed to raise our
hands when we had a thought.

00:01:20.940 --> 00:01:22.540 align:middle line:10%
Our Zen master
stood in the corner.

00:01:22.540 --> 00:01:25.000 align:middle line:84%
In his hand he carried
an 18-inch bamboo stick

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:26.160 align:middle line:90%
known as a keisaku.

00:01:26.160 --> 00:01:28.816 align:middle line:84%
And when we raised our hands,
he would thwack us on the back.

00:01:28.816 --> 00:01:31.440 align:middle line:84%
So I only stayed in that school
of mediation a couple of weeks.

00:01:31.440 --> 00:01:32.273 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my gosh.

00:01:32.273 --> 00:01:34.240 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Found myself
lying to my Zen master.

00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:37.550 align:middle line:84%
When you're lying to your Zen
master, it's time to move on.

00:01:37.550 --> 00:01:41.510 align:middle line:10%
So I moved on to Vipassana
and Buddhist meditation, Zen

00:01:41.510 --> 00:01:45.100 align:middle line:10%
biofeedback, and chakra
meditations, and energy

00:01:45.100 --> 00:01:49.230 align:middle line:10%
meditations, and mindfulness,
and mantra meditations,

00:01:49.230 --> 00:01:51.900 align:middle line:10%
and chocolate
tasting meditations.

00:01:51.900 --> 00:01:54.650 align:middle line:84%
And I found myself
on, off, on, off, on,

00:01:54.650 --> 00:01:59.570 align:middle line:84%
falling off meditation
more than staying with it.

00:01:59.570 --> 00:02:03.320 align:middle line:84%
And then my life got
deeper and deeper

00:02:03.320 --> 00:02:04.910 align:middle line:90%
into the whole corporate world.

00:02:04.910 --> 00:02:07.877 align:middle line:84%
I was a mergers and
acquisitions adviser

00:02:07.877 --> 00:02:09.710 align:middle line:84%
for quite a while working
in the World Trade

00:02:09.710 --> 00:02:11.220 align:middle line:90%
Center in Tower Two.

00:02:11.220 --> 00:02:15.290 align:middle line:84%
And everything in my life
changed pretty much right

00:02:15.290 --> 00:02:16.190 align:middle line:90%
after 9/11.

00:02:16.190 --> 00:02:19.920 align:middle line:84%
I was walking down in SoHo
past a row of cardboard boxes

00:02:19.920 --> 00:02:21.710 align:middle line:90%
that people were living in.

00:02:21.710 --> 00:02:25.750 align:middle line:84%
And a hand reached out, grabbed
my leg, and a face peered up

00:02:25.750 --> 00:02:28.534 align:middle line:84%
and said, "What's gonna
be on your tombstone?"

00:02:28.534 --> 00:02:29.950 align:middle line:84%
It's a fairly
reflective question.

00:02:29.950 --> 00:02:30.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, yes.

00:02:30.860 --> 00:02:33.610 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: So I went home that
night and I said to my wife,

00:02:33.610 --> 00:02:35.600 align:middle line:90%
I don't even know.

00:02:35.600 --> 00:02:37.080 align:middle line:90%
I feel so disconnected.

00:02:37.080 --> 00:02:38.470 align:middle line:90%
I'm unfulfilled.

00:02:38.470 --> 00:02:40.330 align:middle line:84%
My relationships really
aren't fulfilling.

00:02:40.330 --> 00:02:42.310 align:middle line:90%
I'm not doing what I want to do.

00:02:42.310 --> 00:02:45.270 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well, Deepak
Chopra is doing a meditation

00:02:45.270 --> 00:02:47.710 align:middle line:84%
retreat right now
in Oxford, England.

00:02:47.710 --> 00:02:48.710 align:middle line:90%
You should check it out.

00:02:48.710 --> 00:02:50.590 align:middle line:90%
So the next day, I quit my job.

00:02:50.590 --> 00:02:53.110 align:middle line:84%
Within a month, I had headed
off to Oxford, hung out

00:02:53.110 --> 00:02:54.280 align:middle line:90%
with Deepak, meditated.

00:02:54.280 --> 00:02:56.050 align:middle line:90%
He advised me to go to India.

00:02:56.050 --> 00:02:57.510 align:middle line:84%
Did my own eat,
pray, love thing,

00:02:57.510 --> 00:03:00.120 align:middle line:90%
without the eating and the love.

00:03:00.120 --> 00:03:01.390 align:middle line:90%
And just the praying.

00:03:01.390 --> 00:03:04.490 align:middle line:84%
And headed off to India
in search of the guru.

00:03:04.490 --> 00:03:06.530 align:middle line:84%
And it was after
six months in India

00:03:06.530 --> 00:03:09.990 align:middle line:84%
that I realized
the guru is inside.

00:03:09.990 --> 00:03:14.480 align:middle line:84%
And that was just like this
profound aha moment for me.

00:03:14.480 --> 00:03:16.390 align:middle line:84%
Came back home, and
a friend of mine

00:03:16.390 --> 00:03:18.766 align:middle line:84%
said, all you do is sit
around and meditate now.

00:03:18.766 --> 00:03:20.390 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, what
am I supposed to do?

00:03:20.390 --> 00:03:22.800 align:middle line:84%
They said, well, you
should teach meditation.

00:03:22.800 --> 00:03:24.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So now, basically,
the interview's over,

00:03:24.800 --> 00:03:27.472 align:middle line:90%
because we just-- [LAUGHS]

00:03:27.472 --> 00:03:28.680 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Thank you so much.

00:03:28.680 --> 00:03:30.138 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I love you,
thank you, bye.

00:03:30.138 --> 00:03:31.880 align:middle line:90%
So, now, let me just back up.

00:03:31.880 --> 00:03:34.574 align:middle line:84%
Why did you start to meditate
in the first place, though?

00:03:34.574 --> 00:03:36.240 align:middle line:84%
You were going through
corporate America

00:03:36.240 --> 00:03:38.300 align:middle line:84%
realizing what-- I
mean, most people

00:03:38.300 --> 00:03:39.500 align:middle line:90%
don't go towards meditation.

00:03:39.500 --> 00:03:41.500 align:middle line:84%
They go towards
alcohol or something.

00:03:41.500 --> 00:03:42.610 align:middle line:84%
I mean, what were you
trying to achieve?

00:03:42.610 --> 00:03:44.318 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Well, I
had touched it before.

00:03:44.318 --> 00:03:47.000 align:middle line:84%
And I had remembered
that whatever

00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:49.610 align:middle line:84%
the style of meditation
that I was doing, even if I

00:03:49.610 --> 00:03:51.280 align:middle line:84%
only stuck with it
a couple of weeks,

00:03:51.280 --> 00:03:53.222 align:middle line:84%
it introduced
balance into my life.

00:03:53.222 --> 00:03:54.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So it worked for you.

00:03:54.430 --> 00:03:57.460 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: So there I was,
a master of the universe,

00:03:57.460 --> 00:04:01.840 align:middle line:84%
working 18 hours a day, 7 days
a week, so out of balance.

00:04:01.840 --> 00:04:05.850 align:middle line:84%
I had traded in my early morning
meditation for an early morning

00:04:05.850 --> 00:04:08.240 align:middle line:84%
train ride to the
World Trade Center.

00:04:08.240 --> 00:04:12.320 align:middle line:84%
I had traded in my evening
meditation for a double scotch.

00:04:12.320 --> 00:04:15.060 align:middle line:84%
And like that, balance
was gone from my life.

00:04:15.060 --> 00:04:18.200 align:middle line:84%
In my mind I knew,
oh, I remember

00:04:18.200 --> 00:04:19.700 align:middle line:90%
those days of meditating.

00:04:19.700 --> 00:04:21.110 align:middle line:90%
I was balanced.

00:04:21.110 --> 00:04:22.041 align:middle line:90%
I was happier.

00:04:22.041 --> 00:04:24.290 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Were you, when you
were in that corporate job,

00:04:24.290 --> 00:04:26.300 align:middle line:84%
and mergers and acqs
are pretty difficult

00:04:26.300 --> 00:04:30.220 align:middle line:84%
and it gets pretty tense, were
you ever feeling discontent,

00:04:30.220 --> 00:04:32.230 align:middle line:84%
that there was something
that was wrong,

00:04:32.230 --> 00:04:35.950 align:middle line:84%
that there were things
occurring around you didn't feel

00:04:35.950 --> 00:04:37.330 align:middle line:90%
were right with you?

00:04:37.330 --> 00:04:39.790 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Yeah, absolutely.

00:04:39.790 --> 00:04:45.500 align:middle line:84%
I truly felt that my dharma
had been lost in the shuffle,

00:04:45.500 --> 00:04:48.210 align:middle line:84%
and that I was working
just to make money.

00:04:48.210 --> 00:04:51.480 align:middle line:84%
Which is fine, if that's
what you're trying to do,

00:04:51.480 --> 00:04:52.610 align:middle line:90%
work to make money.

00:04:52.610 --> 00:04:53.190 align:middle line:90%
That's great.

00:04:53.190 --> 00:04:55.167 align:middle line:84%
Then you should keep
moving in that direction.

00:04:55.167 --> 00:04:57.000 align:middle line:84%
But that wasn't really
what was in my heart.

00:04:57.000 --> 00:04:59.620 align:middle line:90%
I was working to be fulfilled.

00:04:59.620 --> 00:05:01.620 align:middle line:84%
And so there was
a giant disconnect

00:05:01.620 --> 00:05:03.980 align:middle line:84%
in terms of what's
going on inside me

00:05:03.980 --> 00:05:05.720 align:middle line:84%
and what's going
on outside of me.

00:05:05.720 --> 00:05:07.650 align:middle line:84%
And I think when
your inner dialogue

00:05:07.650 --> 00:05:11.180 align:middle line:84%
and your outer dialogue don't
match up, it's a lot of work.

00:05:11.180 --> 00:05:13.654 align:middle line:84%
And you can get burnt out,
and you can get so depressed.

00:05:13.654 --> 00:05:14.820 align:middle line:90%
And there's so many things--

00:05:14.820 --> 00:05:15.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Sidetracked.

00:05:15.050 --> 00:05:16.020 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: --that
can pull you down.

00:05:16.020 --> 00:05:16.609 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:05:16.609 --> 00:05:17.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:20.190 align:middle line:84%
You're speaking to many that are
going through that experience

00:05:20.190 --> 00:05:21.330 align:middle line:90%
right now.

00:05:21.330 --> 00:05:23.450 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: I think most
people are doing that.

00:05:23.450 --> 00:05:25.002 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That are
trying to recover

00:05:25.002 --> 00:05:26.460 align:middle line:84%
from the recession,
that are trying

00:05:26.460 --> 00:05:29.380 align:middle line:84%
to make ends meet in a
very unfulfilled job,

00:05:29.380 --> 00:05:32.040 align:middle line:84%
realizing that the things
that they are supporting

00:05:32.040 --> 00:05:34.890 align:middle line:84%
are harmful to maybe
themselves or the environment

00:05:34.890 --> 00:05:35.930 align:middle line:90%
or other people.

00:05:35.930 --> 00:05:37.460 align:middle line:84%
And they don't know
how to get out.

00:05:37.460 --> 00:05:40.150 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: And I think pain can
be a very powerful motivator.

00:05:40.150 --> 00:05:41.640 align:middle line:84%
I think when you're
really feeling

00:05:41.640 --> 00:05:43.820 align:middle line:84%
the depths of your
darkness, that's

00:05:43.820 --> 00:05:46.340 align:middle line:84%
enough to get you off
the couch to take a step.

00:05:46.340 --> 00:05:47.560 align:middle line:90%
For some people, it's not.

00:05:47.560 --> 00:05:49.950 align:middle line:84%
But for me, it was
really, I was like,

00:05:49.950 --> 00:05:52.660 align:middle line:84%
you know what, I'm in
so much pain right now,

00:05:52.660 --> 00:05:54.250 align:middle line:90%
just show me anything else.

00:05:54.250 --> 00:05:59.210 align:middle line:84%
And so that opportunity
to find a new path--

00:05:59.210 --> 00:06:00.490 align:middle line:90%
I knew what I didn't want.

00:06:00.490 --> 00:06:01.990 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know what
I did want, but I

00:06:01.990 --> 00:06:04.000 align:middle line:90%
knew what wasn't serving me.

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:06.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What did you
say to the company

00:06:06.560 --> 00:06:08.980 align:middle line:84%
you were working with at the
time when you wanted to quit?

00:06:08.980 --> 00:06:10.220 align:middle line:90%
What did you say?

00:06:10.220 --> 00:06:12.700 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: I said, I
think I'm leaving here.

00:06:12.700 --> 00:06:16.930 align:middle line:84%
And of course, every
one of my fellow masters

00:06:16.930 --> 00:06:18.500 align:middle line:84%
of the universe--
You know, these

00:06:18.500 --> 00:06:20.860 align:middle line:84%
are people who are
very, very comfortable.

00:06:20.860 --> 00:06:21.910 align:middle line:90%
Everyone's got an MBA.

00:06:21.910 --> 00:06:26.500 align:middle line:84%
Everyone has a really nice
pedigree or a nice credential.

00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:31.100 align:middle line:84%
And everyone's making
a beautiful living

00:06:31.100 --> 00:06:33.100 align:middle line:84%
and able to provide
for their families,

00:06:33.100 --> 00:06:34.860 align:middle line:90%
for generations to come.

00:06:34.860 --> 00:06:36.490 align:middle line:90%
And everyone's working hard.

00:06:36.490 --> 00:06:39.100 align:middle line:84%
But on the other
end of that, I was

00:06:39.100 --> 00:06:41.220 align:middle line:84%
perceived as being
absolutely crazy.

00:06:41.220 --> 00:06:44.400 align:middle line:84%
Why would anyone
step away from this?

00:06:44.400 --> 00:06:47.732 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That was the desirable
thing to do at the time.

00:06:47.732 --> 00:06:48.440 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Right.

00:06:48.440 --> 00:06:51.290 align:middle line:84%
And for me, it just
wasn't working.

00:06:51.290 --> 00:06:54.400 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure for most of them, it
still works many years later.

00:06:54.400 --> 00:06:58.100 align:middle line:84%
But for me, I had
to explore further.

00:06:58.100 --> 00:07:02.770 align:middle line:84%
There was something that I
wasn't feeling or sensing

00:07:02.770 --> 00:07:05.670 align:middle line:84%
or connecting with, and I
needed to take that step.

00:07:05.670 --> 00:07:09.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So when you went to
the retreat that Deepak did,

00:07:09.430 --> 00:07:13.010 align:middle line:84%
what was it that made sense
to you there as opposed

00:07:13.010 --> 00:07:15.690 align:middle line:84%
to all the medication
that you had studied?

00:07:15.690 --> 00:07:18.370 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Well, I had gone
to the retreat with such

00:07:18.370 --> 00:07:20.190 align:middle line:84%
a heavy heart, such
a weight on my chest,

00:07:20.190 --> 00:07:23.876 align:middle line:84%
so emotionally I
was very, very sad.

00:07:23.876 --> 00:07:27.200 align:middle line:84%
All my relationships
were struggling.

00:07:27.200 --> 00:07:30.580 align:middle line:84%
They were caustic
and abrasive at best.

00:07:30.580 --> 00:07:32.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Makes sense,
because you were not

00:07:32.470 --> 00:07:34.430 align:middle line:84%
doing your heart's
fulfillment at the time.

00:07:34.430 --> 00:07:37.190 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: And I was
just trying to do my job

00:07:37.190 --> 00:07:38.990 align:middle line:90%
and get it done with.

00:07:38.990 --> 00:07:43.040 align:middle line:84%
And at the same time, I
suddenly had this opportunity

00:07:43.040 --> 00:07:47.070 align:middle line:84%
to connect to
stillness and silence.

00:07:47.070 --> 00:07:51.790 align:middle line:84%
It was as if my heart was
this white linen cloth that

00:07:51.790 --> 00:07:54.370 align:middle line:84%
had been immersed
in black India ink.

00:07:54.370 --> 00:07:56.980 align:middle line:84%
But each day of meditating
and hanging out with Deepak,

00:07:56.980 --> 00:08:01.670 align:middle line:84%
I actually was draping that
cloth through a rushing stream.

00:08:01.670 --> 00:08:03.640 align:middle line:90%
And I became a little lighter.

00:08:03.640 --> 00:08:05.450 align:middle line:90%
And I forgave myself.

00:08:05.450 --> 00:08:09.230 align:middle line:90%
And I opened my heart to love.

00:08:09.230 --> 00:08:12.400 align:middle line:84%
And just within a few days,
I felt as light as a feather,

00:08:12.400 --> 00:08:14.210 align:middle line:90%
after I'd been so heavy.

00:08:14.210 --> 00:08:17.340 align:middle line:84%
And I was somewhat
traumatized by 9/11.

00:08:17.340 --> 00:08:20.550 align:middle line:84%
I lost a lot of friends,
and I was no longer

00:08:20.550 --> 00:08:22.700 align:middle line:84%
in the World Trade
Center during 9/11.

00:08:22.700 --> 00:08:23.830 align:middle line:90%
But you can imagine--

00:08:23.830 --> 00:08:24.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You left right before.

00:08:24.360 --> 00:08:26.680 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Yeah, I left
about six months before.

00:08:26.680 --> 00:08:30.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so that experience
is also very shocking.

00:08:30.190 --> 00:08:31.740 align:middle line:84%
It was shocking to
the entire world.

00:08:31.740 --> 00:08:32.448 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Right.

00:08:32.448 --> 00:08:35.049 align:middle line:84%
That's got its own list
of different aspects.

00:08:35.049 --> 00:08:38.175 align:middle line:84%
But I truly felt
for the first time--

00:08:38.175 --> 00:08:41.080 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't just 9/11-- but
I felt for the first time,

00:08:41.080 --> 00:08:43.730 align:middle line:90%
oh, my heart is so light.

00:08:43.730 --> 00:08:47.680 align:middle line:84%
My spirit really wants to
connect on a deeper level.

00:08:47.680 --> 00:08:49.200 align:middle line:84%
And then Deepak
said to me, well,

00:08:49.200 --> 00:08:50.780 align:middle line:90%
you need to check out India.

00:08:50.780 --> 00:08:52.390 align:middle line:90%
It's amazing there.

00:08:52.390 --> 00:08:54.960 align:middle line:84%
So I was like, OK,
I'll go to India.

00:08:54.960 --> 00:08:57.070 align:middle line:84%
And I left right
from Oxford, England

00:08:57.070 --> 00:08:58.810 align:middle line:90%
and headed off to India.

00:08:58.810 --> 00:09:00.840 align:middle line:84%
And I searched high
and low and went

00:09:00.840 --> 00:09:02.730 align:middle line:84%
to find His Holiness
in Dharamsala,

00:09:02.730 --> 00:09:05.570 align:middle line:90%
and he wasn't there then.

00:09:05.570 --> 00:09:08.370 align:middle line:84%
But I cruised all over,
talking to roadside rishis.

00:09:08.370 --> 00:09:10.030 align:middle line:90%
I had a-ha moments.

00:09:10.030 --> 00:09:11.470 align:middle line:90%
I had all this wild stuff.

00:09:11.470 --> 00:09:14.069 align:middle line:84%
And I was laying in a
hammock in a cashew forest

00:09:14.069 --> 00:09:15.610 align:middle line:84%
in Karala, reading
the Bhagavad Gita,

00:09:15.610 --> 00:09:19.190 align:middle line:84%
chapter two, verse 48, which
I had read, I don't know,

00:09:19.190 --> 00:09:19.990 align:middle line:90%
1,000 times.

00:09:19.990 --> 00:09:24.385 align:middle line:84%
But this time when I read it,
"yoga-sthah kuru karmani."

00:09:24.385 --> 00:09:26.315 align:middle line:84%
It's where Krishna
is talking to Arjuna,

00:09:26.315 --> 00:09:30.440 align:middle line:84%
and he's like, establish
yourself in yoga-sthah,

00:09:30.440 --> 00:09:34.360 align:middle line:84%
in the present moment,
in union, in oneness.

00:09:34.360 --> 00:09:37.490 align:middle line:84%
"Kuru"-- then perform--
"karmani"-- action.

00:09:37.490 --> 00:09:39.580 align:middle line:90%
So I was like, yes, of course.

00:09:39.580 --> 00:09:41.430 align:middle line:90%
The guru rests inside.

00:09:41.430 --> 00:09:43.245 align:middle line:84%
The answer to every
question rests inside.

00:09:43.245 --> 00:09:48.570 align:middle line:84%
And I had this amazing aha
moment, and raced up to Mumbai,

00:09:48.570 --> 00:09:49.410 align:middle line:90%
flew back home.

00:09:49.410 --> 00:09:50.006 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Left.

00:09:50.006 --> 00:09:52.380 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: And I was just
like, I've got it, I've got it!

00:09:52.380 --> 00:09:53.350 align:middle line:90%
The guru's inside.

00:09:53.350 --> 00:09:54.400 align:middle line:90%
I can stop looking.

00:09:54.400 --> 00:09:57.300 align:middle line:84%
I can stop seeking
everything outside of me.

00:09:57.300 --> 00:10:00.780 align:middle line:84%
But what I realized is, yes,
the answer to every question

00:10:00.780 --> 00:10:04.900 align:middle line:84%
is inside, but only if you quiet
yourself down enough to hear

00:10:04.900 --> 00:10:07.970 align:middle line:84%
those whispers of God, or
the whispers of your heart.

00:10:07.970 --> 00:10:10.310 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That is the
most challenging part,

00:10:10.310 --> 00:10:11.472 align:middle line:90%
for me at least.

00:10:11.472 --> 00:10:12.930 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: I think
for most people.

00:10:12.930 --> 00:10:13.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Why?

00:10:13.430 --> 00:10:16.240 align:middle line:84%
Why for most people is that
the most challenging part?

00:10:16.240 --> 00:10:19.360 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Because we live
here in this modern world where

00:10:19.360 --> 00:10:22.050 align:middle line:84%
it's [SNAPPING]--
come on, get it done,

00:10:22.050 --> 00:10:24.660 align:middle line:84%
especially if you're from the
East Coast or the West Coast.

00:10:24.660 --> 00:10:25.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And you're from?

00:10:25.880 --> 00:10:28.390 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: I'm from
Queens originally.

00:10:28.390 --> 00:10:31.812 align:middle line:84%
I live in Carlsbad, California,
the sweet spot of the universe.

00:10:31.812 --> 00:10:33.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because
there's so similar.

00:10:33.270 --> 00:10:34.435 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Yes, exactly.

00:10:34.435 --> 00:10:35.800 align:middle line:90%
Identical.

00:10:35.800 --> 00:10:38.870 align:middle line:84%
Carlsbad doesn't
really have culture,

00:10:38.870 --> 00:10:40.440 align:middle line:84%
doesn't really
have amazing food,

00:10:40.440 --> 00:10:43.450 align:middle line:84%
doesn't really have any finance,
doesn't have any fashion,

00:10:43.450 --> 00:10:45.190 align:middle line:84%
doesn't have
sophisticated music.

00:10:45.190 --> 00:10:47.990 align:middle line:84%
But it's got the weather, and
it's got that ocean breeze,

00:10:47.990 --> 00:10:48.640 align:middle line:90%
and we do.

00:10:48.640 --> 00:10:52.310 align:middle line:84%
Our culture is
LEGOLAND and Comic-Con.

00:10:52.310 --> 00:10:55.874 align:middle line:84%
So it's a big shift from
East Coast to Carlsbad.

00:10:55.874 --> 00:10:57.290 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Coming
from Queens though,

00:10:57.290 --> 00:10:59.860 align:middle line:84%
did you ever bring any of
that experience with you

00:10:59.860 --> 00:11:01.760 align:middle line:90%
into the meditation?

00:11:01.760 --> 00:11:02.781 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Of course.

00:11:02.781 --> 00:11:03.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How?

00:11:03.280 --> 00:11:05.740 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: I think we're
all brought up in New York

00:11:05.740 --> 00:11:09.260 align:middle line:84%
to-- First of all,
that there can only

00:11:09.260 --> 00:11:12.800 align:middle line:84%
be one winner in
any conversation.

00:11:12.800 --> 00:11:14.810 align:middle line:84%
We're taught that New
York City certainly

00:11:14.810 --> 00:11:17.430 align:middle line:90%
is the center of the universe.

00:11:17.430 --> 00:11:18.180 align:middle line:90%
And it is.

00:11:18.180 --> 00:11:20.290 align:middle line:84%
I think we would all
acknowledge that.

00:11:20.290 --> 00:11:22.830 align:middle line:84%
And at the same time,
I think that there's

00:11:22.830 --> 00:11:25.160 align:middle line:84%
some amazing
opportunities for us

00:11:25.160 --> 00:11:29.540 align:middle line:84%
to realize that we are
such conditioned beings.

00:11:29.540 --> 00:11:35.700 align:middle line:84%
We are all beings of condition
and practicing something

00:11:35.700 --> 00:11:37.300 align:middle line:90%
over and over and over.

00:11:37.300 --> 00:11:38.950 align:middle line:84%
And so we're not
very reflective.

00:11:38.950 --> 00:11:40.040 align:middle line:90%
We're reflexive.

00:11:40.040 --> 00:11:42.060 align:middle line:84%
We're not very purposeful
with our actions.

00:11:42.060 --> 00:11:43.260 align:middle line:90%
We're knee-jerk.

00:11:43.260 --> 00:11:46.430 align:middle line:84%
And that really allowed
me, being from Queens

00:11:46.430 --> 00:11:48.760 align:middle line:84%
and seeing that all
around me, and knowing

00:11:48.760 --> 00:11:52.486 align:middle line:84%
that we have 60,000 to
80,000 thoughts a day.

00:11:52.486 --> 00:11:54.110 align:middle line:84%
And of course, in
Queens you would say,

00:11:54.110 --> 00:11:57.516 align:middle line:84%
or in New York City you would
say, I probably have more.

00:11:57.516 --> 00:12:02.280 align:middle line:84%
Just because that's the
vibe of that whole world.

00:12:02.280 --> 00:12:04.870 align:middle line:84%
But I do a lot of
work in the city,

00:12:04.870 --> 00:12:07.451 align:middle line:84%
and I do a lot of work in
the corporate world training

00:12:07.451 --> 00:12:07.950 align:middle line:90%
people.

00:12:07.950 --> 00:12:10.454 align:middle line:84%
I do a lot of work with the
military and law enforcement.

00:12:10.454 --> 00:12:12.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: When you say
you work with them,

00:12:12.120 --> 00:12:14.685 align:middle line:84%
what is the main thing
that you're there to teach?

00:12:14.685 --> 00:12:17.060 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: I teach people how
to connect to the stillness

00:12:17.060 --> 00:12:18.885 align:middle line:90%
and silence that rests within.

00:12:18.885 --> 00:12:22.214 align:middle line:84%
I teach people to
trust their silence,

00:12:22.214 --> 00:12:23.380 align:middle line:90%
because that's what happens.

00:12:23.380 --> 00:12:26.320 align:middle line:84%
We pull up a light, we can't
even sit there for two seconds

00:12:26.320 --> 00:12:29.430 align:middle line:84%
without fidgeting around or
texting or doing whatever.

00:12:29.430 --> 00:12:32.660 align:middle line:84%
We're in this
environment where we're

00:12:32.660 --> 00:12:36.480 align:middle line:84%
taught as we come
out of the womb,

00:12:36.480 --> 00:12:39.070 align:middle line:84%
the doctor who delivers you
whispers it into your ear,

00:12:39.070 --> 00:12:42.750 align:middle line:84%
OK, here's how it
works, effort and focus.

00:12:42.750 --> 00:12:43.570 align:middle line:90%
It's not working?

00:12:43.570 --> 00:12:44.930 align:middle line:90%
More effort, more focus.

00:12:44.930 --> 00:12:46.190 align:middle line:90%
Oh, it's still not working?

00:12:46.190 --> 00:12:47.750 align:middle line:90%
More effort, more focus.

00:12:47.750 --> 00:12:53.360 align:middle line:84%
And we're never taught, trust,
surrender, connect, listen.

00:12:53.360 --> 00:12:56.640 align:middle line:84%
There's this
beautiful line, do you

00:12:56.640 --> 00:13:00.550 align:middle line:84%
have the patience to wait
until your mud settles?

00:13:00.550 --> 00:13:04.830 align:middle line:84%
Do you have the patience to
wait until you water is clear

00:13:04.830 --> 00:13:08.820 align:middle line:84%
and the right action
arises by itself?

00:13:08.820 --> 00:13:12.200 align:middle line:84%
No one in New York has that
patience, not inherently.

00:13:12.200 --> 00:13:16.125 align:middle line:84%
And no one who's really working
hard and making stuff happen,

00:13:16.125 --> 00:13:19.370 align:middle line:84%
using their winning
formula has that patience.

00:13:19.370 --> 00:13:22.020 align:middle line:84%
And this is a whole 'nother
conversation coming in.

00:13:22.020 --> 00:13:25.060 align:middle line:84%
Can you just chill for a little
bit and let things unfold?

00:13:25.060 --> 00:13:26.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, this
is the first time

00:13:26.560 --> 00:13:30.250 align:middle line:84%
I've heard this term, crisis
meditation, that you teach.

00:13:30.250 --> 00:13:33.115 align:middle line:84%
And first of all,
you don't teach it.

00:13:33.115 --> 00:13:35.200 align:middle line:84%
But tell me what
crisis meditation is.

00:13:35.200 --> 00:13:37.880 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Well, most of
us are crisis meditators.

00:13:37.880 --> 00:13:42.120 align:middle line:84%
But that's similar to being
like a crisis toothbrusher.

00:13:42.120 --> 00:13:45.150 align:middle line:84%
We brush our teeth from
we're five years old

00:13:45.150 --> 00:13:47.210 align:middle line:84%
and they teach us,
OK, brush your teeth.

00:13:47.210 --> 00:13:48.890 align:middle line:84%
And we don't really
like to do it.

00:13:48.890 --> 00:13:51.590 align:middle line:84%
Our parents keep saying, or our
caregivers tell us to do that.

00:13:51.590 --> 00:13:53.294 align:middle line:84%
We wet the brush,
we make believe,

00:13:53.294 --> 00:13:54.710 align:middle line:84%
and then at a
certain point we go,

00:13:54.710 --> 00:13:58.830 align:middle line:84%
oh, this helps me keep my
teeth, and I'm used to it now,

00:13:58.830 --> 00:14:02.230 align:middle line:84%
and my breath is fresher,
and it feels good,

00:14:02.230 --> 00:14:03.615 align:middle line:90%
and we've ritualized it.

00:14:03.615 --> 00:14:05.970 align:middle line:90%
We've created the routine.

00:14:05.970 --> 00:14:10.850 align:middle line:84%
Meditation, very few people
proactively sit down and do it.

00:14:10.850 --> 00:14:12.450 align:middle line:84%
Imagine if you brushed
your teeth only

00:14:12.450 --> 00:14:14.330 align:middle line:84%
when the dentist told
you you had a cavity.

00:14:14.330 --> 00:14:15.320 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, right, right.

00:14:15.320 --> 00:14:16.770 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Then you would
have not teeth left.

00:14:16.770 --> 00:14:18.728 align:middle line:84%
And that's what most
people do with meditation.

00:14:18.728 --> 00:14:20.880 align:middle line:84%
So what I do is I
help people bring

00:14:20.880 --> 00:14:25.670 align:middle line:84%
some very specific routines
and rituals into their life

00:14:25.670 --> 00:14:30.230 align:middle line:84%
so they can not meditate when
the crisis suddenly comes.

00:14:30.230 --> 00:14:31.740 align:middle line:84%
Because most people,
they're living

00:14:31.740 --> 00:14:34.460 align:middle line:84%
their lives and everything's
fine, and suddenly crisis,

00:14:34.460 --> 00:14:38.740 align:middle line:84%
and you magically find
spirituality in that moment.

00:14:38.740 --> 00:14:42.470 align:middle line:84%
And you could probably, if you
were meditating in advance,

00:14:42.470 --> 00:14:44.490 align:middle line:90%
it wouldn't even be a crisis.

00:14:44.490 --> 00:14:46.390 align:middle line:84%
Since I'm meditating
every single day,

00:14:46.390 --> 00:14:47.890 align:middle line:84%
and it's going on
about 12 years,

00:14:47.890 --> 00:14:51.750 align:middle line:84%
twice a day, crises
don't happen to me.

00:14:51.750 --> 00:14:53.840 align:middle line:84%
I see things, well,
that's a disappointment,

00:14:53.840 --> 00:14:56.490 align:middle line:84%
oh, that's an uncertainty,
oh, that's a surprise.

00:14:56.490 --> 00:14:59.100 align:middle line:84%
But it's almost like it's
coming at me in slow motion.

00:14:59.100 --> 00:15:00.880 align:middle line:84%
And so I teach
law enforcement, I

00:15:00.880 --> 00:15:03.540 align:middle line:84%
teach the military to
help them step away

00:15:03.540 --> 00:15:07.420 align:middle line:84%
from all that swirl of
60,000 to 80,000 thoughts,

00:15:07.420 --> 00:15:10.260 align:middle line:84%
and trust themselves,
trust out there.

00:15:10.260 --> 00:15:12.500 align:middle line:84%
And it's not a woo-woo
kind of conversation.

00:15:12.500 --> 00:15:16.360 align:middle line:84%
It's truly slowing yourself
down and connecting

00:15:16.360 --> 00:15:19.320 align:middle line:84%
to who you really are,
not the conditioned layers

00:15:19.320 --> 00:15:20.290 align:middle line:90%
that are around you.

00:15:20.290 --> 00:15:22.267 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's kind of
untraining the mind.

00:15:22.267 --> 00:15:24.100 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: It's exactly
untraining the mind.

00:15:24.100 --> 00:15:26.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, because
we are so conditioned

00:15:26.430 --> 00:15:29.500 align:middle line:84%
to jump on or fix
or focus and do

00:15:29.500 --> 00:15:32.850 align:middle line:84%
what it is that it
does almost take effort

00:15:32.850 --> 00:15:34.400 align:middle line:90%
to untrain the mind.

00:15:34.400 --> 00:15:36.224 align:middle line:84%
But when you do it,
it's effortless.

00:15:36.224 --> 00:15:37.140 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Absolutely.

00:15:37.140 --> 00:15:39.180 align:middle line:90%
So it takes a little practice.

00:15:39.180 --> 00:15:40.980 align:middle line:90%
It takes showing up.

00:15:40.980 --> 00:15:42.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Let's talk
about the practices,

00:15:42.660 --> 00:15:45.730 align:middle line:84%
because we like to grab
onto concepts in our minds.

00:15:45.730 --> 00:15:47.240 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Let's make it real.

00:15:47.240 --> 00:15:48.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So we have
names for these things.

00:15:48.990 --> 00:15:51.490 align:middle line:84%
One of them you call
metta meditation.

00:15:51.490 --> 00:15:52.922 align:middle line:90%
OK, so what is metta meditation?

00:15:52.922 --> 00:15:55.130 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: So let's say you
really angry at somebody.

00:15:55.130 --> 00:15:58.430 align:middle line:84%
Let's say your harboring a
grievance or some resentment.

00:15:58.430 --> 00:16:00.430 align:middle line:84%
Metta meditation
is, actually, it's

00:16:00.430 --> 00:16:03.140 align:middle line:84%
the very, very first step
of Buddhist meditations.

00:16:03.140 --> 00:16:05.510 align:middle line:84%
This doesn't mean you
have to become a Buddhist.

00:16:05.510 --> 00:16:07.460 align:middle line:84%
This doesn't mean you
have to pay homage

00:16:07.460 --> 00:16:09.470 align:middle line:90%
to some deity or god.

00:16:09.470 --> 00:16:12.480 align:middle line:84%
This essentially means--
metta means loving kindness.

00:16:12.480 --> 00:16:15.590 align:middle line:84%
So let's say you're feeling
a little blame-y or finger

00:16:15.590 --> 00:16:17.880 align:middle line:90%
pointy at somebody.

00:16:17.880 --> 00:16:20.620 align:middle line:84%
And I start every day
with a metta meditation.

00:16:20.620 --> 00:16:22.030 align:middle line:90%
And so you breathe in.

00:16:22.030 --> 00:16:23.910 align:middle line:90%
And it's a breathing technique.

00:16:23.910 --> 00:16:25.510 align:middle line:84%
Breathing techniques
are so powerful,

00:16:25.510 --> 00:16:26.801 align:middle line:90%
because no equipment necessary.

00:16:26.801 --> 00:16:28.780 align:middle line:90%
We have it all built in.

00:16:28.780 --> 00:16:31.200 align:middle line:10%
And so you slowly breathe
in through your nostril,

00:16:31.200 --> 00:16:33.250 align:middle line:10%
and you allow that breath
to come into you, down

00:16:33.250 --> 00:16:36.220 align:middle line:10%
into your belly, and you
actually breath in metta.

00:16:36.220 --> 00:16:39.100 align:middle line:10%
You breathe in loving
kindness from the universe.

00:16:39.100 --> 00:16:40.820 align:middle line:10%
And when you flow
it back out you

00:16:40.820 --> 00:16:42.770 align:middle line:10%
flow it back out
to your teachers.

00:16:42.770 --> 00:16:44.760 align:middle line:10%
Then you do it
again, one more time.

00:16:44.760 --> 00:16:47.505 align:middle line:10%
Breathe it in, fill
your heart with metta,

00:16:47.505 --> 00:16:50.750 align:middle line:10%
loving kindness, universal
unconditional love.

00:16:50.750 --> 00:16:52.550 align:middle line:84%
When you flow it
out, you flow it out

00:16:52.550 --> 00:16:54.560 align:middle line:90%
to your family and your friends.

00:16:54.560 --> 00:16:56.750 align:middle line:84%
You do that one more
time, breathe it in,

00:16:56.750 --> 00:16:58.550 align:middle line:84%
and then you flow
it out to those

00:16:58.550 --> 00:17:01.849 align:middle line:90%
with whom you have a grievance.

00:17:01.849 --> 00:17:03.640 align:middle line:84%
And you don't stop to
think, wait a second,

00:17:03.640 --> 00:17:05.420 align:middle line:84%
who's this person
and what's going on?

00:17:05.420 --> 00:17:06.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What's the grievance?

00:17:06.050 --> 00:17:06.758 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Right.

00:17:06.758 --> 00:17:10.410 align:middle line:84%
Just next breath in, you breathe
in that same loving kindness

00:17:10.410 --> 00:17:14.750 align:middle line:84%
and flow it out to every single
sentient being on the planet.

00:17:14.750 --> 00:17:16.510 align:middle line:84%
And then with you
last breath in,

00:17:16.510 --> 00:17:18.763 align:middle line:84%
you flow it to every
corner of the galaxy.

00:17:18.763 --> 00:17:20.304 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it gets
larger and larger.

00:17:20.304 --> 00:17:21.262 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Gets larger.

00:17:21.262 --> 00:17:24.280 align:middle line:84%
And then you take all that
love from every single corner

00:17:24.280 --> 00:17:26.839 align:middle line:84%
of the cosmos, and
breathe it in, and then

00:17:26.839 --> 00:17:28.580 align:middle line:90%
just release it again.

00:17:28.580 --> 00:17:29.650 align:middle line:90%
That could take what?

00:17:29.650 --> 00:17:31.500 align:middle line:90%
A minute, 5 minutes, 10 minutes?

00:17:31.500 --> 00:17:33.470 align:middle line:90%
However long you'd like.

00:17:33.470 --> 00:17:35.810 align:middle line:84%
And who doesn't
feel like they want

00:17:35.810 --> 00:17:38.047 align:middle line:90%
the universe to kiss their soul?

00:17:38.047 --> 00:17:40.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Who doesn't feel good
after something like that?

00:17:40.380 --> 00:17:42.020 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: So in
that moment, even

00:17:42.020 --> 00:17:46.220 align:middle line:84%
if you were just
vindictive or angry,

00:17:46.220 --> 00:17:48.530 align:middle line:84%
at least for those few
moments, you're not anymore.

00:17:48.530 --> 00:17:49.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No.

00:17:49.030 --> 00:17:52.620 align:middle line:84%
That's beautiful, because
there's past hurts or family

00:17:52.620 --> 00:17:55.400 align:middle line:84%
members you haven't spoken to
because of stupid things that

00:17:55.400 --> 00:17:55.950 align:middle line:90%
happen.

00:17:55.950 --> 00:17:57.320 align:middle line:90%
I mean, we do that.

00:17:57.320 --> 00:17:59.020 align:middle line:84%
And we take years
before we speak

00:17:59.020 --> 00:18:00.960 align:middle line:90%
to people over stupid things.

00:18:00.960 --> 00:18:03.710 align:middle line:84%
So this could really help
you take the high road

00:18:03.710 --> 00:18:04.942 align:middle line:90%
on that type of situation.

00:18:04.942 --> 00:18:07.400 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: You don't have to
call them up and forgive them.

00:18:07.400 --> 00:18:10.150 align:middle line:84%
And you don't have to call them
up and beg for forgiveness.

00:18:10.150 --> 00:18:12.740 align:middle line:84%
Really all you're doing
is establishing your flow

00:18:12.740 --> 00:18:13.990 align:middle line:90%
for the day.

00:18:13.990 --> 00:18:14.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:18:14.850 --> 00:18:17.050 align:middle line:84%
And now, is this also
a breathing meditation?

00:18:17.050 --> 00:18:19.280 align:middle line:84%
There's also breathing
meditation that you teach.

00:18:19.280 --> 00:18:19.905 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Yes.

00:18:19.905 --> 00:18:22.060 align:middle line:10%
Well, one of the most
beautiful meditations

00:18:22.060 --> 00:18:24.930 align:middle line:10%
that I teach I call it
16 seconds to bliss.

00:18:24.930 --> 00:18:27.200 align:middle line:10%
But when I'm teaching the
military or law enforcement,

00:18:27.200 --> 00:18:30.760 align:middle line:10%
I call it 16 seconds to clarity.

00:18:30.760 --> 00:18:32.795 align:middle line:10%
Sometimes I call it
tactical breathing.

00:18:32.795 --> 00:18:34.170 align:middle line:84%
It's a very
different experience.

00:18:34.170 --> 00:18:35.294 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Know your audience.

00:18:35.294 --> 00:18:36.254 align:middle line:90%
Nope, that's fine.

00:18:36.254 --> 00:18:38.170 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Languaging
is so important with all

00:18:38.170 --> 00:18:39.545 align:middle line:84%
these teachings,
because that's I

00:18:39.545 --> 00:18:41.310 align:middle line:84%
think what turns
so many people off.

00:18:41.310 --> 00:18:43.464 align:middle line:84%
If it sounds too woo-woo
or if it sounds like,

00:18:43.464 --> 00:18:45.130 align:middle line:84%
oh no, I'm not going
to connect to that,

00:18:45.130 --> 00:18:46.520 align:middle line:90%
then they won't show up.

00:18:46.520 --> 00:18:47.510 align:middle line:90%
So here's how it works.

00:18:47.510 --> 00:18:50.037 align:middle line:84%
You envision a
current grievance.

00:18:50.037 --> 00:18:51.870 align:middle line:84%
You don't go back to
your childhood traumas.

00:18:51.870 --> 00:18:53.070 align:middle line:90%
It's not therapy.

00:18:53.070 --> 00:18:55.940 align:middle line:84%
But you just really want to like
maybe someone disappointed you

00:18:55.940 --> 00:18:57.260 align:middle line:90%
this week.

00:18:57.260 --> 00:19:00.460 align:middle line:84%
And so you envision
them in your mind's eye.

00:19:00.460 --> 00:19:01.860 align:middle line:90%
You actually see that person.

00:19:01.860 --> 00:19:04.310 align:middle line:84%
And you can actually even
feel place in your body

00:19:04.310 --> 00:19:06.440 align:middle line:90%
that's disturbing a little bit.

00:19:06.440 --> 00:19:10.650 align:middle line:84%
And then close your eyes
and for four seconds

00:19:10.650 --> 00:19:12.310 align:middle line:84%
slowly breathe in
through your nostril

00:19:12.310 --> 00:19:17.270 align:middle line:84%
and observe, witness your breath
as it comes into your sinuses

00:19:17.270 --> 00:19:19.820 align:middle line:84%
through your chest
down into your belly.

00:19:19.820 --> 00:19:22.230 align:middle line:84%
And then you hold it
there for four seconds,

00:19:22.230 --> 00:19:26.250 align:middle line:84%
and then witness it,
observe it, watch it.

00:19:26.250 --> 00:19:29.480 align:middle line:84%
And then you allow it to come
back up, move up your chest,

00:19:29.480 --> 00:19:31.060 align:middle line:84%
into your throat,
into your sinuses,

00:19:31.060 --> 00:19:32.990 align:middle line:90%
out through your nostrils.

00:19:32.990 --> 00:19:34.980 align:middle line:84%
And then you watch
it as it dissipates.

00:19:34.980 --> 00:19:35.810 align:middle line:90%
You observe it.

00:19:35.810 --> 00:19:37.890 align:middle line:90%
You witness it.

00:19:37.890 --> 00:19:40.380 align:middle line:84%
In those 16 seconds
you're not in the past,

00:19:40.380 --> 00:19:41.780 align:middle line:90%
you're not in the future.

00:19:41.780 --> 00:19:43.360 align:middle line:90%
You're fully present.

00:19:43.360 --> 00:19:46.370 align:middle line:84%
It's impossible to
have thoughts and file

00:19:46.370 --> 00:19:48.570 align:middle line:90%
your breath simultaneously.

00:19:48.570 --> 00:19:54.160 align:middle line:84%
Now maybe, in second 17 you're
back with all your grievance.

00:19:54.160 --> 00:19:56.220 align:middle line:84%
But we just had a
pattern interrupt.

00:19:56.220 --> 00:19:57.797 align:middle line:90%
We do it with our iPhones.

00:19:57.797 --> 00:19:58.880 align:middle line:90%
We do it with our laptops.

00:19:58.880 --> 00:20:00.280 align:middle line:90%
We do it with our computers.

00:20:00.280 --> 00:20:02.490 align:middle line:90%
We power them down, reboot.

00:20:02.490 --> 00:20:04.850 align:middle line:90%
We don't reboot ourselves.

00:20:04.850 --> 00:20:06.192 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Everyone has 16 seconds.

00:20:06.192 --> 00:20:06.900 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Right.

00:20:06.900 --> 00:20:09.410 align:middle line:84%
Even the people who claim,
no no, I'm very, very busy.

00:20:09.410 --> 00:20:10.960 align:middle line:90%
I don't got it.

00:20:10.960 --> 00:20:11.900 align:middle line:90%
Everyone has it.

00:20:11.900 --> 00:20:16.490 align:middle line:84%
And so for those
who-- Oprah has it.

00:20:16.490 --> 00:20:19.160 align:middle line:90%
Barack Obama has it.

00:20:19.160 --> 00:20:20.324 align:middle line:90%
Richard Branson has it.

00:20:20.324 --> 00:20:21.490 align:middle line:90%
These are famous meditators.

00:20:21.490 --> 00:20:23.180 align:middle line:90%
Deepak Chopra has it.

00:20:23.180 --> 00:20:27.800 align:middle line:84%
If they have 16
seconds, so do we.

00:20:27.800 --> 00:20:31.545 align:middle line:84%
If I'm teaching a yoga crowd,
I call it 16 seconds to ananda.

00:20:31.545 --> 00:20:33.045 align:middle line:84%
But if I'm teaching
law enforcement,

00:20:33.045 --> 00:20:34.990 align:middle line:90%
it's 16 seconds to clarity.

00:20:34.990 --> 00:20:37.796 align:middle line:90%
And they love it.

00:20:37.796 --> 00:20:39.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, one of the
things that I noticed

00:20:39.670 --> 00:20:42.330 align:middle line:84%
here is that it kind of allows
you to distance yourself

00:20:42.330 --> 00:20:47.490 align:middle line:84%
from a situation that might be
happening and to, as you said,

00:20:47.490 --> 00:20:51.960 align:middle line:84%
what was the word you said,
to bring it to a place

00:20:51.960 --> 00:20:55.250 align:middle line:84%
where it doesn't affect you as
easily, that you can actually

00:20:55.250 --> 00:20:57.920 align:middle line:84%
observe it before
it comes at you.

00:20:57.920 --> 00:21:01.830 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: When we can view
parts of our life as a witness,

00:21:01.830 --> 00:21:07.600 align:middle line:84%
then we can truly
experience a disconnection

00:21:07.600 --> 00:21:10.170 align:middle line:90%
from our emotional turbulence.

00:21:10.170 --> 00:21:10.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:21:10.710 --> 00:21:11.410 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:21:11.410 --> 00:21:12.570 align:middle line:90%
So we're learning here.

00:21:12.570 --> 00:21:15.250 align:middle line:90%
What is the sensory meditation?

00:21:15.250 --> 00:21:17.430 align:middle line:10%
>>DAVIDJI: Well see, the
reason that a lot of people

00:21:17.430 --> 00:21:19.500 align:middle line:10%
don't show up for
meditation is because they

00:21:19.500 --> 00:21:22.650 align:middle line:10%
think you have to sit in
utpluthih, full lotus.

00:21:22.650 --> 00:21:24.430 align:middle line:10%
Your eyes have to be closed.

00:21:24.430 --> 00:21:26.710 align:middle line:10%
You have to sit in
a certain space.

00:21:26.710 --> 00:21:31.350 align:middle line:84%
You have to repeat the magic
sound over and over again.

00:21:31.350 --> 00:21:33.730 align:middle line:84%
And that doesn't work
for a lot of people.

00:21:33.730 --> 00:21:35.560 align:middle line:84%
There's 8 billion
people on the planet.

00:21:35.560 --> 00:21:39.370 align:middle line:84%
We each have to find our access
point to stillness and silence.

00:21:39.370 --> 00:21:43.080 align:middle line:84%
So sensory meditation
allows us to connect

00:21:43.080 --> 00:21:45.360 align:middle line:90%
to aromas that are around us.

00:21:45.360 --> 00:21:49.450 align:middle line:84%
Even a massage is a form
of sensory meditation.

00:21:49.450 --> 00:21:52.916 align:middle line:84%
Most of us, we get a massage,
and then we're out cold.

00:21:52.916 --> 00:21:55.040 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly it's like,
are you still massaging me?

00:21:55.040 --> 00:21:57.910 align:middle line:90%
I just levitated off the table.

00:21:57.910 --> 00:22:04.070 align:middle line:84%
So if we can realize that,
that's a sensory meditation.

00:22:04.070 --> 00:22:08.755 align:middle line:84%
It's a practice whether
that's just breathing in lilac

00:22:08.755 --> 00:22:11.130 align:middle line:84%
or breathing in
lavender, breathing

00:22:11.130 --> 00:22:15.990 align:middle line:84%
in something that truly calms
you, such as sandalwood, rose,

00:22:15.990 --> 00:22:19.045 align:middle line:84%
especially for Pittas
in Ayurveda, those who

00:22:19.045 --> 00:22:21.160 align:middle line:84%
are, like, totally
fired up, and fire's

00:22:21.160 --> 00:22:22.470 align:middle line:90%
coming out of their fingers.

00:22:22.470 --> 00:22:26.380 align:middle line:84%
These types of citrus, rose,
lavender, patchouli even,

00:22:26.380 --> 00:22:28.370 align:middle line:84%
vanilla, sandalwood,
they're very,

00:22:28.370 --> 00:22:30.090 align:middle line:84%
very grounding and
very, very slowing.

00:22:30.090 --> 00:22:34.357 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, you can have a
whole meditative experience.

00:22:34.357 --> 00:22:36.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Through smell,
through aromatherapy.

00:22:36.190 --> 00:22:37.102 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:22:37.102 --> 00:22:37.810 align:middle line:90%
It's interesting.

00:22:37.810 --> 00:22:39.625 align:middle line:84%
I interviewed a
neuroscientist who

00:22:39.625 --> 00:22:42.920 align:middle line:84%
has done many studies on the
brain and meditation-- Andy

00:22:42.920 --> 00:22:43.620 align:middle line:90%
Newberg.

00:22:43.620 --> 00:22:46.770 align:middle line:84%
And he actually can see
the SPECT scan studies

00:22:46.770 --> 00:22:51.420 align:middle line:84%
of different meditations and
how it impacts individual brains

00:22:51.420 --> 00:22:52.220 align:middle line:90%
differently.

00:22:52.220 --> 00:22:54.390 align:middle line:84%
So what you're saying
has wonderful validity

00:22:54.390 --> 00:22:55.920 align:middle line:84%
in the neuroscience
world as well,

00:22:55.920 --> 00:22:57.830 align:middle line:90%
because people are different.

00:22:57.830 --> 00:22:59.220 align:middle line:90%
We all are different.

00:22:59.220 --> 00:23:03.680 align:middle line:84%
And things impact us differently
and reward us differently.

00:23:03.680 --> 00:23:07.270 align:middle line:84%
I know someone exactly like
that, who is so enhanced by

00:23:07.270 --> 00:23:11.820 align:middle line:84%
smells that it puts her in
a totally different place.

00:23:11.820 --> 00:23:13.957 align:middle line:90%
So that makes perfect sense.

00:23:13.957 --> 00:23:15.540 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Some of
us are very visual.

00:23:15.540 --> 00:23:17.100 align:middle line:90%
Some of us are very olfactory.

00:23:17.100 --> 00:23:20.840 align:middle line:84%
Some of us are very kinesthetic
and very tactile related.

00:23:20.840 --> 00:23:22.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Those are different
forms of meditation.

00:23:22.890 --> 00:23:24.770 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: We need to find
the one that works for us.

00:23:24.770 --> 00:23:26.228 align:middle line:84%
And so one could
say, oh, you know,

00:23:26.228 --> 00:23:28.860 align:middle line:84%
I tried and fell off
the wagon 30 times.

00:23:28.860 --> 00:23:31.476 align:middle line:84%
And then suddenly
you say, smell this.

00:23:31.476 --> 00:23:33.400 align:middle line:84%
And they suddenly
are transported,

00:23:33.400 --> 00:23:35.520 align:middle line:84%
and they're fully
present, and it works.

00:23:35.520 --> 00:23:38.160 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's whatever gets
us to the place of presence,

00:23:38.160 --> 00:23:41.490 align:middle line:84%
however it can in
a meditation realm.

00:23:41.490 --> 00:23:45.420 align:middle line:84%
And it gets us because that
is such a break for the stress

00:23:45.420 --> 00:23:48.320 align:middle line:84%
levels in the body and
for the nervous system.

00:23:48.320 --> 00:23:51.550 align:middle line:84%
And it enhances immunity,
because it releases

00:23:51.550 --> 00:23:54.360 align:middle line:84%
all those great
endorphins of those

00:23:54.360 --> 00:23:57.441 align:middle line:84%
feel good chemicals in the body
that really do repair and heal.

00:23:57.441 --> 00:23:59.190 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: And there's
so many studies now

00:23:59.190 --> 00:24:01.564 align:middle line:84%
that prove that meditation
changes the physical structure

00:24:01.564 --> 00:24:06.630 align:middle line:84%
of the brain, studies that
show that meditation allows us

00:24:06.630 --> 00:24:09.670 align:middle line:84%
to bully less and to feel
that we're more connected

00:24:09.670 --> 00:24:12.370 align:middle line:84%
to each other
through gamma waves

00:24:12.370 --> 00:24:16.630 align:middle line:84%
and through other types of waves
that come into our physiology

00:24:16.630 --> 00:24:17.730 align:middle line:90%
when we're meditating.

00:24:17.730 --> 00:24:19.250 align:middle line:84%
We've now proven
that whole process.

00:24:19.250 --> 00:24:19.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:24:19.750 --> 00:24:22.550 align:middle line:84%
Isn't that amazing, that all
these great scientific studies

00:24:22.550 --> 00:24:24.040 align:middle line:84%
have come out around something
that you've been doing

00:24:24.040 --> 00:24:25.650 align:middle line:84%
and that many have been
doing for centuries?

00:24:25.650 --> 00:24:28.100 align:middle line:84%
But you know, the scientific
