I worked in the corporate
swirl for 20 years,

00:35:08.200 --> 00:35:12.620 align:middle line:10%
but I didn't have the tools to
be the calm amidst the chaos.

00:35:12.620 --> 00:35:17.070 align:middle line:10%
In the wake of 9/11, I left that
world and set out on a journey

00:35:17.070 --> 00:35:20.920 align:middle line:10%
to uncover the timeless
secrets of inner piece

00:35:20.920 --> 00:35:22.180 align:middle line:10%
and personal transformation.

00:35:22.180 --> 00:35:25.000 align:middle line:10%


00:35:25.000 --> 00:35:29.160 align:middle line:10%
I met world-renowned teacher,
author, and spiritual adviser

00:35:29.160 --> 00:35:29.915 align:middle line:10%
Deepak Chopra.

00:35:29.915 --> 00:35:32.720 align:middle line:10%


00:35:32.720 --> 00:35:34.910 align:middle line:10%
For 10 years, I travel
the world with him,

00:35:34.910 --> 00:35:39.540 align:middle line:10%
sat at the feet of the masters,
studied the ancient texts,

00:35:39.540 --> 00:35:43.490 align:middle line:10%
and began sharing these
timeless tools and techniques

00:35:43.490 --> 00:35:47.810 align:middle line:10%
with thousands
throughout the world.

00:35:47.810 --> 00:35:52.110 align:middle line:10%
And now, I'm sharing
them with you,

00:35:52.110 --> 00:35:57.078 align:middle line:10%
so you can more fully enjoy
what matters most in life.

00:35:57.078 --> 00:36:41.990 align:middle line:90%


00:36:41.990 --> 00:36:45.230 align:middle line:10%
My story of transformation
is your story.

00:36:45.230 --> 00:36:47.800 align:middle line:10%
Your struggles have
been my struggles.

00:36:47.800 --> 00:36:50.180 align:middle line:10%
Your challenges have been mine.

00:36:50.180 --> 00:36:52.760 align:middle line:10%
And now these timeless
secrets are ours.

00:36:52.760 --> 00:37:10.290 align:middle line:90%


00:37:10.290 --> 00:37:10.790 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: OK.

00:37:10.790 --> 00:37:13.250 align:middle line:84%
So now that we
understand that there

00:37:13.250 --> 00:37:15.790 align:middle line:84%
are various types of
meditations that really work

00:37:15.790 --> 00:37:18.100 align:middle line:84%
for us, that we can
make them practical,

00:37:18.100 --> 00:37:20.490 align:middle line:84%
I'm really interested in what
you talked about in terms

00:37:20.490 --> 00:37:25.060 align:middle line:84%
of sound and meditation
through sound.

00:37:25.060 --> 00:37:29.960 align:middle line:84%
Can different types
of music really elicit

00:37:29.960 --> 00:37:31.680 align:middle line:84%
that type of feeling
that you really

00:37:31.680 --> 00:37:36.830 align:middle line:84%
get from a chanting meditation
or, what you mentioned,

00:37:36.830 --> 00:37:38.154 align:middle line:90%
Kamasutra meditation?

00:37:38.154 --> 00:37:39.820 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: It's really
a great question,

00:37:39.820 --> 00:37:43.770 align:middle line:84%
because we figure we're in
the womb for nine months,

00:37:43.770 --> 00:37:46.710 align:middle line:84%
and so we're hearing that
drumbeat of our mother's heart

00:37:46.710 --> 00:37:48.740 align:middle line:90%
for nine months, constantly.

00:37:48.740 --> 00:37:52.840 align:middle line:84%
And ideally, that's a very
comforting and grounding

00:37:52.840 --> 00:37:53.632 align:middle line:90%
environment for us.

00:37:53.632 --> 00:37:55.673 align:middle line:84%
Then we come back out into
the rest of the world,

00:37:55.673 --> 00:37:58.150 align:middle line:84%
where there's all this other
crazy, kooky stuff, noises

00:37:58.150 --> 00:38:00.260 align:middle line:84%
that don't necessarily
nourish us.

00:38:00.260 --> 00:38:02.360 align:middle line:84%
And so when we can
get the opportunity

00:38:02.360 --> 00:38:07.260 align:middle line:84%
to connect to music,
connect to a beat,

00:38:07.260 --> 00:38:09.910 align:middle line:84%
connect to a flow
of sound waves--

00:38:09.910 --> 00:38:13.710 align:middle line:84%
Sound healing is one of the
most powerful present moment--

00:38:13.710 --> 00:38:16.120 align:middle line:84%
because it takes us
into the present moment.

00:38:16.120 --> 00:38:18.510 align:middle line:84%
It takes us away from
every other thing that

00:38:18.510 --> 00:38:21.960 align:middle line:84%
could be bothering us, or
scaring us, or making the sad,

00:38:21.960 --> 00:38:23.780 align:middle line:90%
and brings us back to the womb.

00:38:23.780 --> 00:38:26.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Imagine when
we were in the womb.

00:38:26.430 --> 00:38:27.796 align:middle line:90%
You're immersed in water.

00:38:27.796 --> 00:38:29.420 align:middle line:84%
If you've ever been
in a swimming pool,

00:38:29.420 --> 00:38:32.730 align:middle line:84%
and you hear music from
underneath the swimming pool,

00:38:32.730 --> 00:38:36.650 align:middle line:84%
and it's like a dullened
sound, but you really

00:38:36.650 --> 00:38:38.000 align:middle line:90%
get the vibration of it.

00:38:38.000 --> 00:38:40.786 align:middle line:84%
It probably goes through
the water to you.

00:38:40.786 --> 00:38:42.410 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, that's exactly
what we felt like.

00:38:42.410 --> 00:38:45.070 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: We're used to hearing
things just through our ears,

00:38:45.070 --> 00:38:47.400 align:middle line:84%
not really aware that the
vibrations are touching

00:38:47.400 --> 00:38:49.100 align:middle line:84%
every single cell
in our physiology.

00:38:49.100 --> 00:38:50.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:38:50.080 --> 00:38:52.120 align:middle line:84%
So you created something
called-- what is it,

00:38:52.120 --> 00:38:53.014 align:middle line:90%
Ayurvedic opera?

00:38:53.014 --> 00:38:53.680 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Yeah.

00:38:53.680 --> 00:38:55.610 align:middle line:84%
About a year ago I wrote
an Ayurvedic opera.

00:38:55.610 --> 00:38:56.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What is that?

00:38:56.700 --> 00:38:59.180 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: So
Ayurveda acknowledges

00:38:59.180 --> 00:39:02.130 align:middle line:84%
that the mahabhutas, the five
master elements-- space, air,

00:39:02.130 --> 00:39:05.580 align:middle line:84%
fire, water, and earth--
are flowing outside of us

00:39:05.580 --> 00:39:07.410 align:middle line:90%
in a most universal context.

00:39:07.410 --> 00:39:10.240 align:middle line:84%
And they're flowing
into us as well.

00:39:10.240 --> 00:39:13.560 align:middle line:84%
So space is all about
infinite possibilities.

00:39:13.560 --> 00:39:16.370 align:middle line:84%
Air is all about
movement and change.

00:39:16.370 --> 00:39:18.720 align:middle line:84%
Fire is all about
transformation.

00:39:18.720 --> 00:39:20.420 align:middle line:90%
Water is about nourishment.

00:39:20.420 --> 00:39:22.650 align:middle line:90%
And earth is about stability.

00:39:22.650 --> 00:39:26.740 align:middle line:84%
So I wrote this opera, sort of
like a spiritual song cycle,

00:39:26.740 --> 00:39:30.680 align:middle line:84%
about weaving those five
elements through this process.

00:39:30.680 --> 00:39:33.050 align:middle line:84%
And Ayurveda's the
5,000-year-old science

00:39:33.050 --> 00:39:33.920 align:middle line:90%
of healing.

00:39:33.920 --> 00:39:37.750 align:middle line:84%
And so I connected with
sound healers, Sacred Fire,

00:39:37.750 --> 00:39:39.240 align:middle line:90%
they're a Canadian group.

00:39:39.240 --> 00:39:41.450 align:middle line:84%
And we took my
libretto and turned it

00:39:41.450 --> 00:39:46.290 align:middle line:84%
into this really amazing
healing mantras and music

00:39:46.290 --> 00:39:48.484 align:middle line:90%
and meditations.

00:39:48.484 --> 00:39:49.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you're
a musician also.

00:39:49.900 --> 00:39:51.900 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Just to a
very, very small extent.

00:39:51.900 --> 00:39:53.930 align:middle line:84%
I would never say that
to real musicians.

00:39:53.930 --> 00:39:55.721 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, we could
take a look at this.

00:39:55.721 --> 00:39:56.710 align:middle line:90%
We'll be the judge.

00:39:56.710 --> 00:39:59.626 align:middle line:84%
In this video, take a look
at this Ayurvedic opera.

00:39:59.626 --> 00:40:01.500 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: It's called
"Journey to Infinity."

00:40:01.500 --> 00:40:02.848 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Sounds cool.

00:40:02.848 --> 00:40:04.342 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:40:04.342 --> 00:40:07.540 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Journey to infinity
is a profound experience.

00:40:07.540 --> 00:40:09.520 align:middle line:90%
It's like channeling the divine.

00:40:09.520 --> 00:40:12.737 align:middle line:90%
Emotionally, it's cathartic.

00:40:12.737 --> 00:40:14.198 align:middle line:90%
It's healing.

00:40:14.198 --> 00:40:16.146 align:middle line:90%
It's nourishing.

