00:43:14.930 --> 00:43:18.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you have taught
about the myths of meditation.

00:43:18.200 --> 00:43:20.242 align:middle line:84%
What are some of the myths
around the meditation?

00:43:20.242 --> 00:43:22.033 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: That's really
one of the reasons

00:43:22.033 --> 00:43:23.840 align:middle line:84%
that I wrote Secrets
of Meditation,

00:43:23.840 --> 00:43:28.930 align:middle line:84%
because I felt that so many
people stopped meditating

00:43:28.930 --> 00:43:32.780 align:middle line:84%
or didn't meditate because
they had a misconception.

00:43:32.780 --> 00:43:35.070 align:middle line:84%
And so I really had
gone on this journey

00:43:35.070 --> 00:43:38.440 align:middle line:84%
to demystify all of the
myths that prevent people

00:43:38.440 --> 00:43:41.470 align:middle line:84%
from accessing the
stillness that rests within.

00:43:41.470 --> 00:43:42.406 align:middle line:90%
So myth number one.

00:43:42.406 --> 00:43:44.280 align:middle line:84%
What we probably all
learned about meditation

00:43:44.280 --> 00:43:46.840 align:middle line:84%
by watching David Carradine
on "Kung Fu" with Kwai Chang

00:43:46.840 --> 00:43:48.470 align:middle line:90%
and Grasshopper.

00:43:48.470 --> 00:43:50.530 align:middle line:84%
Or we watch Jim Carrey
levitate in the jungle

00:43:50.530 --> 00:43:52.360 align:middle line:90%
with the guano and the monkey.

00:43:52.360 --> 00:43:54.720 align:middle line:90%
Or we read something about it.

00:43:54.720 --> 00:43:59.360 align:middle line:84%
But all of those teachings would
say, oh, you want to meditate?

00:43:59.360 --> 00:44:03.310 align:middle line:84%
OK, first stop your thoughts
and clear your mind.

00:44:03.310 --> 00:44:04.019 align:middle line:90%
As if.

00:44:04.019 --> 00:44:05.060 align:middle line:90%
That's not even possible.

00:44:05.060 --> 00:44:06.685 align:middle line:84%
I don't even know
what that even means.

00:44:06.685 --> 00:44:08.260 align:middle line:90%
What do you clear the mind with?

00:44:08.260 --> 00:44:08.969 align:middle line:90%
The mind clearer?

00:44:08.969 --> 00:44:10.760 align:middle line:84%
And then you have
another one, and then you

00:44:10.760 --> 00:44:11.610 align:middle line:90%
have to clear that.

00:44:11.610 --> 00:44:14.460 align:middle line:84%
And so suddenly there's all
these mind clearers stacked up.

00:44:14.460 --> 00:44:18.680 align:middle line:84%
And so we can't clear the mind
and we can't stop thoughts.

00:44:18.680 --> 00:44:20.760 align:middle line:84%
In fact, consciousness-based
teachings

00:44:20.760 --> 00:44:23.770 align:middle line:90%
never tell you to stop this.

00:44:23.770 --> 00:44:26.510 align:middle line:84%
They just tell
you to drift here.

00:44:26.510 --> 00:44:31.290 align:middle line:84%
And by drifting here, this
doesn't really exist anymore.

00:44:31.290 --> 00:44:34.612 align:middle line:84%
And so that's why 16 seconds
to bliss actually works.

00:44:34.612 --> 00:44:36.570 align:middle line:84%
And that's why all these
other techniques where

00:44:36.570 --> 00:44:39.740 align:middle line:84%
we drift our attention
to here suddenly work,

00:44:39.740 --> 00:44:42.800 align:middle line:84%
because it's not about
stopping anything else.

00:44:42.800 --> 00:44:45.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That is so
relieving, because I

00:44:45.050 --> 00:44:47.050 align:middle line:90%
have a busy mind over here.

00:44:47.050 --> 00:44:49.100 align:middle line:84%
So I don't really
know how to do that.

00:44:49.100 --> 00:44:50.240 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: So you're
probably meditating,

00:44:50.240 --> 00:44:52.710 align:middle line:84%
and you're making lists, and
you're feeling like a loser,

00:44:52.710 --> 00:44:53.140 align:middle line:90%
and you're like--

00:44:53.140 --> 00:44:55.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I sit down to meditate,
and then I have a thought,

00:44:55.320 --> 00:44:57.069 align:middle line:84%
and then I get distracted
by that thought,

00:44:57.069 --> 00:44:59.080 align:middle line:84%
and I forgot that I
was going to meditate.

00:44:59.080 --> 00:45:00.580 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Three
hours later, you're

00:45:00.580 --> 00:45:02.790 align:middle line:84%
journaling and doing
all this other stuff.

00:45:02.790 --> 00:45:04.427 align:middle line:90%
That's most people.

00:45:04.427 --> 00:45:06.260 align:middle line:84%
And so we have to give
ourselves permission.

00:45:06.260 --> 00:45:08.450 align:middle line:84%
We're not trying to
clear our thoughts.

00:45:08.450 --> 00:45:10.160 align:middle line:84%
We're not trying
to clear the mind.

00:45:10.160 --> 00:45:12.070 align:middle line:90%
We can't stop them.

00:45:12.070 --> 00:45:13.890 align:middle line:90%
There's one every 1.2 seconds.

00:45:13.890 --> 00:45:15.000 align:middle line:90%
Some of them are cool.

00:45:15.000 --> 00:45:16.676 align:middle line:90%
Some of them are ridiculous.

00:45:16.676 --> 00:45:17.800 align:middle line:90%
Some of them are gibberish.

00:45:17.800 --> 00:45:19.610 align:middle line:90%
Some of them mean nothing.

00:45:19.610 --> 00:45:21.080 align:middle line:90%
But they're coming.

00:45:21.080 --> 00:45:24.710 align:middle line:84%
So if we can bring our attention
to our breath or to a mantra

00:45:24.710 --> 00:45:27.960 align:middle line:84%
or to music or to
something else, whatever

00:45:27.960 --> 00:45:31.010 align:middle line:84%
that object of our
attention is, that's

00:45:31.010 --> 00:45:32.670 align:middle line:84%
one of the secrets
of meditation.

00:45:32.670 --> 00:45:37.110 align:middle line:84%
Just find an object of your
attention, an aroma, a candle,

00:45:37.110 --> 00:45:40.280 align:middle line:90%
tasting a chocolate truffle.

00:45:40.280 --> 00:45:42.800 align:middle line:84%
Repeating Aham
Brahmasmi or some type

00:45:42.800 --> 00:45:46.420 align:middle line:84%
of mantra, a personal
mantra, over and over,

00:45:46.420 --> 00:45:48.850 align:middle line:84%
using an affirmation--
any of those things

00:45:48.850 --> 00:45:52.450 align:middle line:84%
can allow you to create
an object of attention.

00:45:52.450 --> 00:45:54.510 align:middle line:84%
And yes, you'll find
yourself in thought.

00:45:54.510 --> 00:45:57.120 align:middle line:84%
And you can say, oh, I'm
not going to scold myself.

00:45:57.120 --> 00:45:58.350 align:middle line:90%
I'm having a thought.

00:45:58.350 --> 00:46:01.770 align:middle line:84%
I think I'll gently drift back
to the object of my attention.

00:46:01.770 --> 00:46:03.270 align:middle line:84%
And so if that's
your breath, that's

00:46:03.270 --> 00:46:05.657 align:middle line:84%
really what mindfulness
is all about.

00:46:05.657 --> 00:46:06.740 align:middle line:90%
It's taking in everything.

00:46:06.740 --> 00:46:07.956 align:middle line:90%
Sounds aren't distractions.

00:46:07.956 --> 00:46:09.580 align:middle line:84%
They're are all part
of the meditation.

00:46:09.580 --> 00:46:11.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So a major
myth is that you

00:46:11.130 --> 00:46:12.609 align:middle line:84%
don't have to clear
your thoughts.

00:46:12.609 --> 00:46:13.400 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Exactly.

00:46:13.400 --> 00:46:17.910 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You just focus on
what it is that you want.

00:46:17.910 --> 00:46:18.910 align:middle line:90%
Give me another myth.

00:46:18.910 --> 00:46:20.159 align:middle line:90%
That was a good one.

00:46:20.159 --> 00:46:21.450 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: What's another myth?

00:46:21.450 --> 00:46:24.900 align:middle line:84%
Another myth is that-- and this
is a fairly important one--

00:46:24.900 --> 00:46:30.080 align:middle line:84%
if I meditate, I'm a superior
being or I'm enlightened.

00:46:30.080 --> 00:46:33.310 align:middle line:84%
We don't meditate to
become superior beings.

00:46:33.310 --> 00:46:34.210 align:middle line:90%
It's all Namaste.

00:46:34.210 --> 00:46:36.820 align:middle line:84%
We're neither above
nor below anyone.

00:46:36.820 --> 00:46:44.340 align:middle line:84%
And meditation actually doesn't
stop us from being a jerk.

00:46:44.340 --> 00:46:48.160 align:middle line:84%
But it might make us
after the fact go, whoa,

00:46:48.160 --> 00:46:50.610 align:middle line:84%
I don't really want
to behave that way.

00:46:50.610 --> 00:46:52.160 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to act that way.

00:46:52.160 --> 00:46:54.230 align:middle line:84%
And then you may go
back and apologize.

00:46:54.230 --> 00:46:58.680 align:middle line:84%
So His Holiness the Dalai
Lama loses his temper.

00:46:58.680 --> 00:47:00.840 align:middle line:84%
The people we find as
the most spiritual beings

00:47:00.840 --> 00:47:03.670 align:middle line:84%
on the planet
misspeak or mis-act.

00:47:03.670 --> 00:47:06.710 align:middle line:84%
The spiritual journey allows
us to take a step back and say,

00:47:06.710 --> 00:47:09.240 align:middle line:84%
oh, that's not really
how I wanted to show up.

00:47:09.240 --> 00:47:11.060 align:middle line:84%
I think I'll go
back and apologize.

00:47:11.060 --> 00:47:13.560 align:middle line:84%
I think I'll change
the trajectory.

00:47:13.560 --> 00:47:16.580 align:middle line:84%
So the myth is, oh, if
I do this, I'm perfect.

00:47:16.580 --> 00:47:17.360 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:47:17.360 --> 00:47:19.690 align:middle line:84%
You're human, and you'll
always be human, hopefully.

00:47:19.690 --> 00:47:22.148 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Gives you a chance to
reflect on who you are really

00:47:22.148 --> 00:47:24.640 align:middle line:84%
being, and how you react
in certain situations.

00:47:24.640 --> 00:47:25.430 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Yes.

00:47:25.430 --> 00:47:27.388 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You mentioned
earlier that Barack Obama

00:47:27.388 --> 00:47:28.050 align:middle line:90%
is a meditator.

00:47:28.050 --> 00:47:29.100 align:middle line:90%
Really?

00:47:29.100 --> 00:47:32.490 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Well, I don't
know that he calls it that.

00:47:32.490 --> 00:47:35.470 align:middle line:90%
He's a fairly religious guy.

00:47:35.470 --> 00:47:42.850 align:middle line:84%
And he likes to hang out
with spiritual advisers,

00:47:42.850 --> 00:47:44.680 align:middle line:90%
his spiritual advisers.

00:47:44.680 --> 00:47:46.710 align:middle line:84%
I know he's friends with
Deepak Chopra, as well.

00:47:46.710 --> 00:47:53.340 align:middle line:84%
And during the debates between
Barack Obama and Mitt Romney,

00:47:53.340 --> 00:47:55.680 align:middle line:84%
my book got woven
into the White House.

00:47:55.680 --> 00:47:58.280 align:middle line:90%
It may be a coaster there.

00:47:58.280 --> 00:48:00.600 align:middle line:90%
But it got woven in there.

00:48:00.600 --> 00:48:03.630 align:middle line:90%
And he's very reflective.

00:48:03.630 --> 00:48:07.260 align:middle line:84%
And so I bet that he does
some meditation techniques.

00:48:07.260 --> 00:48:10.470 align:middle line:84%
We can see, he's not
necessarily reactive.

00:48:10.470 --> 00:48:12.450 align:middle line:90%
He takes a step back.

00:48:12.450 --> 00:48:15.280 align:middle line:84%
And I like to say if
prayer is talking to God,

00:48:15.280 --> 00:48:16.542 align:middle line:90%
meditation is listening.

00:48:16.542 --> 00:48:17.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, that's wonderful.

00:48:17.750 --> 00:48:19.624 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: So if we can
quiet ourselves down,

00:48:19.624 --> 00:48:21.539 align:middle line:84%
we can actually
hear God responding.

00:48:21.539 --> 00:48:23.080 align:middle line:84%
We can hear the
whispers of our heart

00:48:23.080 --> 00:48:26.230 align:middle line:84%
if we believe in the universe,
as opposed to something else.

00:48:26.230 --> 00:48:30.080 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well I do I really
appreciate the ways that you

00:48:30.080 --> 00:48:32.650 align:middle line:84%
make meditation
practical for everyone.

00:48:32.650 --> 00:48:34.330 align:middle line:84%
And it's caught the
attention of media.

00:48:34.330 --> 00:48:37.860 align:middle line:84%
And you obviously see it
circling different circles

00:48:37.860 --> 00:48:40.450 align:middle line:84%
that we would never
even have thought about.

00:48:40.450 --> 00:48:46.180 align:middle line:84%
Can you teach
children meditation?

00:48:46.180 --> 00:48:48.260 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: One of the
most beautiful things

00:48:48.260 --> 00:48:52.520 align:middle line:84%
that I get to do is I teach
at schools once in a while.

00:48:52.520 --> 00:48:54.560 align:middle line:84%
I don't even use
the word meditation.

00:48:54.560 --> 00:48:58.050 align:middle line:90%
I call it ocean breathing.

00:48:58.050 --> 00:49:01.514 align:middle line:84%
So we're all familiar with
like Ujjayi breathing.

00:49:01.514 --> 00:49:03.680 align:middle line:84%
And so if you don't know
how to do Ujjayi breathing,

00:49:03.680 --> 00:49:05.360 align:middle line:90%
it's a yogic form of breathing.

00:49:05.360 --> 00:49:07.110 align:middle line:84%
But you make believe
your hand is a mirror

00:49:07.110 --> 00:49:09.430 align:middle line:84%
and you go [EXHALES HOARSELY]
and fog the mirror.

00:49:09.430 --> 00:49:13.200 align:middle line:84%
And now you close your
mouth, and now you

00:49:13.200 --> 00:49:15.580 align:middle line:84%
breathe through your
nose, and you essentially

00:49:15.580 --> 00:49:18.520 align:middle line:84%
make that same sound,
almost like your throat

00:49:18.520 --> 00:49:19.170 align:middle line:90%
was the mirror.

00:49:19.170 --> 00:49:29.830 align:middle line:84%
So it's like--
[SLOW, HOARSE BREATHING]

00:49:29.830 --> 00:49:32.294 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you can really feel
that inside of your throat.

00:49:32.294 --> 00:49:33.710 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: If you
close your eyes,

00:49:33.710 --> 00:49:35.251 align:middle line:84%
it's exactly what
it sounds like when

00:49:35.251 --> 00:49:36.860 align:middle line:84%
you're scuba diving
or snorkeling.

00:49:36.860 --> 00:49:40.910 align:middle line:84%
So for kids, we call
it ocean breathing.

00:49:40.910 --> 00:49:42.740 align:middle line:90%
And so kids close their eyes.

00:49:42.740 --> 00:49:44.940 align:middle line:84%
And of course we
say, again, it's

00:49:44.940 --> 00:49:46.840 align:middle line:84%
secretly focusing
on your breath.

00:49:46.840 --> 00:49:47.970 align:middle line:90%
Witness your breath.

00:49:47.970 --> 00:49:50.650 align:middle line:84%
And as they put all that
attention, they're not here,

00:49:50.650 --> 00:49:51.460 align:middle line:90%
they're not there.

00:49:51.460 --> 00:49:53.070 align:middle line:90%
It works with 5-year-olds.

00:49:53.070 --> 00:49:55.380 align:middle line:84%
It works with 15-year-olds,
because it's cool.

00:49:55.380 --> 00:49:58.590 align:middle line:84%
And so when you
start to do that--

00:49:58.590 --> 00:50:02.575 align:middle line:84%
One of my students
is Ariana Grande.

00:50:02.575 --> 00:50:04.872 align:middle line:84%
She's one of the most amazing
vocalists on the planet.

00:50:04.872 --> 00:50:06.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Her voice is amazing.

00:50:06.080 --> 00:50:07.455 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: So
isn't it refreshing

00:50:07.455 --> 00:50:10.180 align:middle line:84%
that someone like that, who's
got all the potential things

00:50:10.180 --> 00:50:11.699 align:middle line:84%
pulling her in a
million directions.

00:50:11.699 --> 00:50:12.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: She's a teenager.

00:50:12.740 --> 00:50:14.530 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: She's meditating.

00:50:14.530 --> 00:50:17.230 align:middle line:84%
And so that allows
her to not get

00:50:17.230 --> 00:50:18.850 align:middle line:90%
distracted by all the things.

00:50:18.850 --> 00:50:23.459 align:middle line:84%
And that's why she actually
acts who she is inside.

00:50:23.459 --> 00:50:24.750 align:middle line:90%
There's a certain authenticity.

00:50:24.750 --> 00:50:26.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You can tell.

00:50:26.060 --> 00:50:29.117 align:middle line:84%
I saw her perform once,
where all of the electronics

00:50:29.117 --> 00:50:30.700 align:middle line:84%
broke down, her
microphone broke down.

00:50:30.700 --> 00:50:34.150 align:middle line:84%
And she was smooth,
completely effortless.

00:50:34.150 --> 00:50:35.690 align:middle line:90%
She just flowed right into it.

00:50:35.690 --> 00:50:38.740 align:middle line:84%
The performer before her, same
technical issues happened,

00:50:38.740 --> 00:50:40.570 align:middle line:90%
she stormed off stage.

00:50:40.570 --> 00:50:42.430 align:middle line:90%
And that makes a lot of sense.

00:50:42.430 --> 00:50:46.320 align:middle line:84%
That's a great example of
seeing how it can actually

00:50:46.320 --> 00:50:49.080 align:middle line:84%
allow you to roll with
the punches even more.

00:50:49.080 --> 00:50:51.270 align:middle line:84%
And that is such
a perfect example

00:50:51.270 --> 00:50:52.690 align:middle line:90%
of why meditation works.

00:50:52.690 --> 00:50:54.400 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to go
to the mountaintop.

00:50:54.400 --> 00:50:55.650 align:middle line:90%
You don't have to wear orange.

00:50:55.650 --> 00:50:57.690 align:middle line:84%
You can actually
get to a place where

00:50:57.690 --> 00:50:59.760 align:middle line:84%
it helps you in
your practical life.

00:50:59.760 --> 00:51:02.830 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to pick up on
something you said, a client.

00:51:02.830 --> 00:51:05.460 align:middle line:84%
You have clients that
you help meditate?

00:51:05.460 --> 00:51:08.069 align:middle line:90%
How does that work?

00:51:08.069 --> 00:51:09.860 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Well, mostly
I work with groups.

00:51:09.860 --> 00:51:13.950 align:middle line:84%
I work with SEAL teams, and
I work with special forces,

00:51:13.950 --> 00:51:17.000 align:middle line:90%
and I work with companies.

00:51:17.000 --> 00:51:20.360 align:middle line:84%
But every once in a while
someone says, listen,

00:51:20.360 --> 00:51:21.610 align:middle line:90%
this is so important to me.

00:51:21.610 --> 00:51:22.960 align:middle line:90%
I want to lock it down.

00:51:22.960 --> 00:51:24.580 align:middle line:90%
I want to get my mantra.

00:51:24.580 --> 00:51:29.280 align:middle line:84%
I want to be able to flow this
through my business, my family,

00:51:29.280 --> 00:51:30.280 align:middle line:90%
my whatever.

00:51:30.280 --> 00:51:32.240 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of times
I'm like, well, just

00:51:32.240 --> 00:51:33.990 align:middle line:84%
come to one of my
workshops or become

00:51:33.990 --> 00:51:35.730 align:middle line:90%
one of my certified instructors.

00:51:35.730 --> 00:51:37.707 align:middle line:84%
So I do teacher trainings,
and I teach people.

00:51:37.707 --> 00:51:40.040 align:middle line:84%
It's called the Masters of
Wisdom and Meditation Teacher

00:51:40.040 --> 00:51:40.840 align:middle line:90%
Training.

00:51:40.840 --> 00:51:42.256 align:middle line:84%
And every once in
a while, someone

00:51:42.256 --> 00:51:44.920 align:middle line:84%
says-- there's like
love a connection,

00:51:44.920 --> 00:51:47.350 align:middle line:84%
just like we have here,
where someone says,

00:51:47.350 --> 00:51:48.520 align:middle line:90%
help me with this process.

00:51:48.520 --> 00:51:50.620 align:middle line:84%
So every once in a
while, we stumble

00:51:50.620 --> 00:51:54.210 align:middle line:84%
into a beautiful
meditation relationship,

00:51:54.210 --> 00:51:56.880 align:middle line:84%
where I teach them pretty
much all my techniques,

00:51:56.880 --> 00:52:01.350 align:middle line:84%
and then we figure out
what works with them.

00:52:01.350 --> 00:52:03.120 align:middle line:84%
Then they keep it
flowing in their lives.

00:52:03.120 --> 00:52:06.030 align:middle line:84%
And so many of my teachers
don't actually teach others.

00:52:06.030 --> 00:52:07.382 align:middle line:90%
They teach it to themselves.

00:52:07.382 --> 00:52:08.840 align:middle line:84%
You really want to
learn something?

00:52:08.840 --> 00:52:10.260 align:middle line:90%
Learn to teach it.

00:52:10.260 --> 00:52:11.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:52:11.800 --> 00:52:15.410 align:middle line:84%
Do people call you to say that
they're really upset, something

00:52:15.410 --> 00:52:17.610 align:middle line:84%
happened that was
horrific, they really help?

00:52:17.610 --> 00:52:20.210 align:middle line:84%
Maybe even a grieving
process or something.

00:52:20.210 --> 00:52:22.800 align:middle line:84%
Do you help them get through
crises in their lives?

00:52:22.800 --> 00:52:25.760 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Sometimes I do.

00:52:25.760 --> 00:52:28.240 align:middle line:84%
I'd rather teach
people all the tools

00:52:28.240 --> 00:52:30.010 align:middle line:90%
than give them the answer.

00:52:30.010 --> 00:52:33.670 align:middle line:84%
I get maybe 50 emails
a day by people saying,

00:52:33.670 --> 00:52:36.450 align:middle line:90%
should dump my loser spouse?

00:52:36.450 --> 00:52:39.440 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not the best person
to answer that question.

00:52:39.440 --> 00:52:42.260 align:middle line:84%
But I can teach them the tools
so that they can actually

00:52:42.260 --> 00:52:45.490 align:middle line:84%
make that decision more
deeply inside and make

00:52:45.490 --> 00:52:46.572 align:middle line:90%
a more conscious choice.

00:52:46.572 --> 00:52:47.530 align:middle line:90%
So that's what I teach.

00:52:47.530 --> 00:52:49.799 align:middle line:84%
I teach people to
make better decisions.

00:52:49.799 --> 00:52:51.590 align:middle line:84%
Doesn't matter to me
what that decision is,

00:52:51.590 --> 00:52:52.967 align:middle line:84%
and I don't want
to convince them

00:52:52.967 --> 00:52:55.300 align:middle line:84%
whether they should open a
business or close of business

00:52:55.300 --> 00:52:59.520 align:middle line:84%
or move out of town or get
divorced or start something.

00:52:59.520 --> 00:53:01.780 align:middle line:84%
But I can teach them the
tools so that they'll

00:53:01.780 --> 00:53:03.850 align:middle line:84%
make the most conscious
choice in that.

00:53:03.850 --> 00:53:05.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And the
tools that you teach

00:53:05.530 --> 00:53:07.500 align:middle line:84%
help people make
better decisions?

00:53:07.500 --> 00:53:08.430 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Yes.

00:53:08.430 --> 00:53:09.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Because?

00:53:09.290 --> 00:53:11.910 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: Because they're not
coming from a reactive space.

00:53:11.910 --> 00:53:14.170 align:middle line:84%
They actually are
being able to come

00:53:14.170 --> 00:53:18.590 align:middle line:84%
from that most genuine space,
which is not conditioned.

00:53:18.590 --> 00:53:21.410 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: To think things through,
and to not regret what you do.

00:53:21.410 --> 00:53:25.549 align:middle line:84%
It does require reflectiveness
and stillness, observation,

00:53:25.549 --> 00:53:27.090 align:middle line:84%
all the things that
you talked about.

00:53:27.090 --> 00:53:28.756 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: It goes
back to that ancient,

00:53:28.756 --> 00:53:31.340 align:middle line:84%
2000-year-old statement,
"yoga-sthah kuru karmani."

00:53:31.340 --> 00:53:34.250 align:middle line:84%
If we can come from
a place of stillness

00:53:34.250 --> 00:53:37.550 align:middle line:84%
as we make a decision,
we'll make better decisions.

00:53:37.550 --> 00:53:41.210 align:middle line:84%
If you see athletes when
the crowd is going crazy,

00:53:41.210 --> 00:53:45.764 align:middle line:84%
someone like LeBron James, on
the line, shooting a foul shot.

00:53:45.764 --> 00:53:47.930 align:middle line:84%
When you see some of these
quarterbacks in football,

00:53:47.930 --> 00:53:49.513 align:middle line:84%
and they're right
about to take it in,

00:53:49.513 --> 00:53:51.560 align:middle line:84%
and 60,000 people
are going crazy,

00:53:51.560 --> 00:53:54.870 align:middle line:84%
and everyone's going crazy, they
are the calm amidst the chaos.

00:53:54.870 --> 00:53:56.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: They are.

00:53:56.030 --> 00:53:56.530 align:middle line:90%
They are.

00:53:56.530 --> 00:53:59.260 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: And they're going
to make the best move, the best

00:53:59.260 --> 00:54:00.420 align:middle line:84%
choice, the best
decision from that.

00:54:00.420 --> 00:54:01.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: They're in the zone.

00:54:01.390 --> 00:54:01.960 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: They're in the zone.

00:54:01.960 --> 00:54:03.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that
zone is what you

00:54:03.430 --> 00:54:05.170 align:middle line:90%
can recreate through meditation.

00:54:05.170 --> 00:54:05.525 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Absolutely.

00:54:05.525 --> 00:54:06.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That you
teach how to do that.

00:54:06.670 --> 00:54:08.211 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: And you're
seeing it more.

00:54:08.211 --> 00:54:10.590 align:middle line:84%
The Super Bowl champs,
the Seattle Seahawks,

00:54:10.590 --> 00:54:12.430 align:middle line:84%
they all started doing
yoga and meditation.

00:54:12.430 --> 00:54:13.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:54:13.090 --> 00:54:14.330 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: And they won.

00:54:14.330 --> 00:54:16.829 align:middle line:84%
I know we're in
Denver right now.

00:54:16.829 --> 00:54:18.620 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Right over
there, they played that.

00:54:18.620 --> 00:54:21.120 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVIDJI: It's not a
very popular conversation.

00:54:21.120 --> 00:54:23.810 align:middle line:84%
But I'm sure after
that, we'll suddenly

00:54:23.810 --> 00:54:27.880 align:middle line:84%
see more and more teams saying,
well, I want that edge as well.

00:54:27.880 --> 00:54:28.920 align:middle line:90%
I want to do that.

00:54:28.920 --> 00:54:32.500 align:middle line:84%
And of course, the LA
Lakers under Phil Jackson,

00:54:32.500 --> 00:54:35.180 align:middle line:84%
he introduced meditation
to all of them.

00:54:35.180 --> 00:54:37.630 align:middle line:84%
He's got a bunch of
rings on his fingers.

00:54:37.630 --> 00:54:38.884 align:middle line:90%
So we know that it works.

00:54:38.884 --> 00:54:40.425 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's
popularizing meditation.

00:54:40.425 --> 00:54:41.240 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: It is.

00:54:41.240 --> 00:54:43.156 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But I did not
know that unless someone

00:54:43.156 --> 00:54:44.230 align:middle line:90%
like you would tell us.

00:54:44.230 --> 00:54:47.515 align:middle line:84%
Because I kind of see that
you walk both worlds here.

00:54:47.515 --> 00:54:48.140 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: Yes.

00:54:48.140 --> 00:54:49.860 align:middle line:84%
And I want to share
it with everyone.

00:54:49.860 --> 00:54:52.560 align:middle line:84%
So whether you're a
heavy metal headbanger

00:54:52.560 --> 00:54:56.510 align:middle line:84%
or whether you're an athlete,
whether you're a business

00:54:56.510 --> 00:55:00.096 align:middle line:84%
person, whether you're a
nanny, whether you're just

00:55:00.096 --> 00:55:03.600 align:middle line:84%
a stay-at-home mom, regardless
of where you are in life,

00:55:03.600 --> 00:55:06.010 align:middle line:84%
you can weave this
into your life

00:55:06.010 --> 00:55:07.581 align:middle line:84%
to take your life
to the next level.

00:55:07.581 --> 00:55:08.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:55:08.080 --> 00:55:11.680 align:middle line:84%
So now you mentioned Navy
SEALs, and you mentioned a lot

00:55:11.680 --> 00:55:13.580 align:middle line:90%
about the military.

00:55:13.580 --> 00:55:16.897 align:middle line:84%
Are these going into any other
different types of practices?

00:55:16.897 --> 00:55:18.480 align:middle line:84%
Are you just teaching
them meditation,

00:55:18.480 --> 00:55:21.477 align:middle line:84%
or do you teach them how
to view into other realms?

00:55:21.477 --> 00:55:22.810 align:middle line:90%
Do you do remote viewing at all?

00:55:22.810 --> 00:55:23.280 align:middle line:90%
>>DAVIDJI: It's funny.

